        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.), and therefore calls upon the Levites not to neglect the performance of their duty. בּני he calls the Levites, addressing them in kindly language; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 1:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. תּשּׁלוּ in Niph. occurs only here, and denotes to avoid a thing from carelessness or laziness, - from שׁלה, to draw forth; ",
